NELLIE'S PEANUT BUTTER COOKIES
1 c. white sugar
2 eggs .
1 c. brown, sugar
1 tsp. vanilla
1 c. margarine
2 tsp. baking soda
1 c. crunchy peanut butter
3 c. flour
Cream margarine, white sugar and brown sugar together. Add peanut butter, vanilla and eggs and beat again. Sift flour and baking soda together and add to mixture. Roll into 1-inch balls and press both ways with floured fork. Bake at 375°, 10 to 12 mins

Listen I’m showing the real life for you. We don’t all have fancy perfectly clean homes. I’ve seen so many “taking down our Christmas decor” videos and these people have maybe 2 pieces of dirt on their floors. I had all kinds of stuff including a clean diaper that found it’s way up under the “tree skirt” which was really just the throw off my bed 🤷‍♀️ I’ve been sick for the last week and still am. Finally got into the doctors and am on the mend. Then add in no water for 5 days and we’ll you just get creative with life. We ate chili out of solo cups the other night 🤷‍♀️. I was hoping our last “tiny living” christmas was going to magical and it had its moments but I can promise you it didn’t go as planned and that’s okay. Life does what it wants to. I’m hoping to slowly finish deep cleaning. You should see my bedroom that’s been our Christmas present storage, wrapping paper, and laundry room area. Remind with no water for 5 days. You cannot walk in there at all the fitted sheet is half way off the bed. Fake snowballs and bows are everywhere and it’s a sea of clothes. I love all the influencers who give us hope and have the “perfect” life but I wanted to stop and remind you it’s okay to be far from it. It’s okay to be “normal” really whatever that may be. Much love from one mom to another 🖤 
#byebyechristmas #byebyedecor #timetoclean #timetoreset #freshslate #reallife #parenthood #motherhoodunfiltered #sahmlifestyle

Honestly making butter is so very easy! If you have a mixer you pour the heavy whipping cream and have it mix til the buttermilk separates from the butter. Then you’ll rinse the butter with water to remove all the excess buttermilk. Season with salt and boom you have butter! If you do not have a mixer pour into jar and shake it like crazy! The same process will happen but more manual labor! Repeat the steps above and there have it butter that you made and know where it came from!

Holy cow 🐮! 
I never dreamed in a million years people would find me interesting!
My name is Katherine. I’m 29 years old and a mom to SIX (yes I know I said 6) I have 5 girls and 1 son and no we didn’t stop when we had our boy. 
I grew up in a very small town in Missouri. I’m the oldest of 10 in a blended family. 
I met my husband online and started dating him the next day, moved in after 2 weeks (and by this I mean we lived in hotels for almost a year) got engaged after 2 months married 1 year later on the dot and quite honestly the rest is history. 
We reside in Kansas and are very slowly building our forever! 
My husband has traveled our entire marriage and it made things hard so we decided to sell the house and buy the camper. We traveled for his job for 2.5 years before starting his own company. 
So right now we are slowly building our forever home. More him than me. 🤣
I’m a very outspoken person, my own worst critic, but also a kind person (I have boundaries though) if I can help someone in any way I will do my best to do so. I post a lot on here and they’ll probably never change.
I like to be funny and real/raw. I joke about our marriage a lot but in fun ways nothing bad! I work for social media. I work from home with a wellness company. I also promote items I truly can stand behind. Flip furniture when I feel like it and a little bit of everything in between. 
No I’m not a spammy sales person and will not blow up your inbox! I do however simply ask that you do not leave me on read 🖤 I know I have something that could help a lot of people financially right now but again I’m not a crazy spammy person so I promise you can like any of my posts without being attacked! 
My favorite color is green I love onions could honestly live off them. I have chickens and quite honestly don’t know why I didn’t talk about them sooner 🤣 you’ll see why!
And goats so many goats 🙌🤣
Slowly working on being more sufficient too! 
I’m your social media best friend you never knew you needed! 
My thoughts are usually random you can kind of tell by my post here! I’m an over the top mom and I have no shame in that either! 
Anyways this is me 🖤

My name is Katherine. I'm 30 years old and a mom to SIX (yes I know I said 6) I have 5 girls and 1 son and no we didn't stop when we had our boy.
I grew up in a very small town in Missouri. I'm the oldest of 10 in a blended family.
I met my husband online and started dating him the next day, moved in after 2 weeks (and by this I mean we lived in hotels for almost a year) got engaged after 2 months married 1 year later on the dot and quite honestly the rest is history.
We reside in Kansas and are very slowly building our forever!
My husband has traveled our entire marriage and it made things hard so we decided to sell the house and buy the camper. We traveled for his job for 2.5 years before starting his own company.
So right now we are slowly building our forever home. More him than me.
I'm a very outspoken person, my own worst critic, but also a kind person (I have boundaries though) if I can help someone in any way I will do my best to do so. I post a lot on here and they'll probably never change.

Imagine the low income apartments, a gold pt cruiser with a clear shower curtain for the back glass, being pregnant, 19 and alone.

Then imagine $43 to live off each week including diapers for your brand new baby. 

Imagine eating a pb&j everyday because making sure that baby was taken care of was the most important thing. 

Now you see that’s my story. That was my start as an “adult”. 

So many see where I’m at now and tell me they can’t do what I do because I have a “following”. That “following” took years and year and a lot of work to build. 

If only you knew how much paint I used, how much vinyl I weeded, how many failed chances I took on myself to get where I am today. 

Don’t compare where your start is compared to the middle of someone else’s story. 

Simply know that you can change your stars. (I know I’m that old to quote that movie) 

You just have to believe in YOU 🖤 #mystory #hope #youcandoit #buildingalifeworthliving
